        <a href="/pages/contact">Contact</a>
      </div>
      <span class="icnav-status"><span class="icnav-status-dot"></span> Open · Fitzrovia</span>
      <a href="#wizard" class="icnav-cta">Get a quote <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      <button type="button" class="icnav-burger" aria-label="Open menu" aria-expanded="false" data-hp-menu-toggle>
        <span class="icnav-burger-bar"></span>
        <span class="icnav-burger-bar"></span>
        <span class="icnav-burger-bar"></span>
      </button>
    </div>
    <div class="icnav-mobile" hidden data-hp-mobile-menu>
      <div class="container">
        <a href="/pages/our-services">Repairs</a>
        <a href="/pages/corporate-service">Corporate</a>
        <a href="/pages/about">Why us</a>
        <a href="/pages/how-it-works">How it works</a>
        <a href="/pages/contact">Contact</a>
        <a href="#wizard" class="icnav-mobile-cta">Get a quote <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
        <div class="icnav-mobile-foot">
          <span class="icnav-status-dot"></span> Open · Fitzrovia
          <a href="tel:+442070998517">+44 (0)207 099 8517</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <button type="button" class="icnav-scrim" hidden aria-label="Close menu" data-hp-menu-scrim></button>
  </nav>

  <div class="hero-morph is-marketing">
    <section class="hp-hero hp-hero-v3 hv-hero-c">
      <div class="container hp-hero-grid hv-hero-c-grid">
        <div class="hv-left">
          <div class="hp-hero-eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> Quote · 60 seconds</div>
          <h1>We repair what they can't.</h1>
          <p class="hp-hero-sub">
            Tell us your model and the symptom — see your price in 60 seconds.
            <span class="hv-sub-more">Genuine parts, two-year warranty, no obligation.</span>
          </p>
          <div class="hv-trustline">
            <span class="hv-stars" aria-hidden="true">{% render 'hp-stars' %}</span>
            <strong>{{ rating }}</strong>
            <span class="hv-trust-sep" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
            <span>{{ review_count }} Google reviews</span>
            <span class="hv-trust-sep" aria-hidden="true">·</span>
            <span>2-year warranty</span>
          </div>
          <div class="hv-c-apple">
            When Apple says "logic board, <span class="strike">{{ apple_board_quote }}</span>" we say "backlight IC, <strong>{{ backlight_price }}</strong>."
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="hv-c-trustcard">
          {% render 'hp-trust-card', rating: rating, review_count: review_count %}
        </div>

        <div class="hv-c-wizard" id="wizard" data-hp-wizard>
          <div class="hv-c-wizard-head">
            <span class="hv-c-wizard-kicker">Instant quote</span>
            <span class="hv-c-wizard-meta">↳ 60 sec · no obligation</span>
          </div>
          <div class="qw-page">
            <div class="qw-progress">
              <div class="qw-progress-top"><div class="qw-mono">Step <span data-hp-step-num>1</span> of 6</div></div>
              <div class="qw-dots">
                {%- assign steps = 'Device,Model,Fault,Issue,Postcode,Quote' | split: ',' -%}
                {%- for step in steps -%}
                  <button type="button" class="qw-dot{% if forloop.first %} current{% endif %}" data-hp-step-dot="{{ forloop.index0 }}" {% unless forloop.first %}disabled{% endunless %}>
                    <span class="qw-dot-num">{{ forloop.index }}</span>
                    <span class="qw-dot-label">{{ step }}</span>
                  </button>
                {%- endfor -%}
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="qw-step" data-hp-step="0">
              <h3 class="qw-step-title">What needs fixing?</h3>
              <p class="qw-step-sub">Pick your device to get started.</p>
              <div class="qw-device-grid">
                <button type="button" class="qw-device-card" data-hp-next>
                  <span class="qw-device-icon">{% render 'hp-icon-phone' %}</span>
                  <span class="qw-device-name">iPhone</span>
                </button>
                <button type="button" class="qw-device-card" data-hp-next>
                  <span class="qw-device-icon">{% render 'hp-icon-monitor' %}</span>
                  <span class="qw-device-name">MacBook</span>
                </button>
                <button type="button" class="qw-device-card" data-hp-next>
                  <span class="qw-device-icon">{% render 'hp-icon-tablet' %}</span>
                  <span class="qw-device-name">iPad</span>
                </button>
                <button type="button" class="qw-device-card" data-hp-next>
                  <span class="qw-device-icon">{% render 'hp-icon-watch' %}</span>
                  <span class="qw-device-name">Watch</span>
                </button>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="qw-step" data-hp-step="1" hidden>
              <button class="qw-btn-back" type="button" data-hp-back>&larr; Back</button>
              <h3 class="qw-step-title">Which model?</h3>
              <p class="qw-step-sub">Pick the closest model group.</p>
              <div class="qw-model-groups">
                <button type="button" class="qw-model-group-head qw-model-group" data-hp-next>
                  <span><span class="qw-model-group-name">Current models</span><span class="qw-model-group-count">M-series and recent devices</span></span>
                  <span class="qw-model-chev">⌄</span>
                </button>
                <button type="button" class="qw-model-group-head qw-model-group" data-hp-next>
                  <span><span class="qw-model-group-name">Older models</span><span class="qw-model-group-count">Intel and legacy devices</span></span>
                  <span class="qw-model-chev">⌄</span>
                </button>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="qw-step" data-hp-step="2" hidden>
              <button class="qw-btn-back" type="button" data-hp-back>&larr; Back</button>
              <h3 class="qw-step-title">What's the issue?</h3>
              <p class="qw-step-sub">Pick the category that best describes the problem.</p>
              <div class="qw-fault-grid">
                <button type="button" class="qw-fault-card" data-hp-next><span class="qw-fault-icon">{% render 'hp-icon-monitor' %}</span><span class="qw-fault-name">Screen</span></button>
                <button type="button" class="qw-fault-card" data-hp-next><span class="qw-fault-icon">{% render 'hp-icon-battery' %}</span><span class="qw-fault-name">Battery</span></button>
                <button type="button" class="qw-fault-card" data-hp-next><span class="qw-fault-icon">{% render 'hp-icon-chip' %}</span><span class="qw-fault-name">Logic board</span></button>
                <button type="button" class="qw-fault-card" data-hp-next><span class="qw-fault-icon">{% render 'hp-icon-droplet' %}</span><span class="qw-fault-name">Liquid damage</span></button>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="qw-step" data-hp-step="3" hidden>
              <button class="qw-btn-back" type="button" data-hp-back>&larr; Back</button>
              <h3 class="qw-step-title">Tell us the symptom.</h3>
              <p class="qw-step-sub">This decides whether it is a fixed repair or a bench diagnosis first.</p>
              <div class="qw-issue-list">
                <button type="button" class="qw-issue-card" data-hp-next><span class="qw-issue-icon-wrap">{% render 'hp-icon-check' %}</span><span class="qw-issue-text"><span class="qw-issue-label">Cracked or failed part</span><span class="qw-issue-hint">Usually fixed-price once the model is known.</span></span></button>
                <button type="button" class="qw-issue-card" data-hp-next><span class="qw-issue-icon-wrap">{% render 'hp-icon-chip' %}</span><span class="qw-issue-text"><span class="qw-issue-label">Won't turn on</span><span class="qw-issue-hint">{{ diagnostic_fee }}, paid at booking, covers bench diagnosis; your repair is quoted separately for approval.</span></span></button>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="qw-step" data-hp-step="4" hidden>
              <button class="qw-btn-back" type="button" data-hp-back>&larr; Back</button>
              <h3 class="qw-step-title">Plan your repair</h3>
              <div class="qw-cfg">
                <div class="qw-cfg-prompt">Enter your postcode to see how soon you can have it back</div>
                <form class="qw-cfg-form" data-hp-next-form>
                  <input class="qw-cfg-input" placeholder="e.g. W1W 8JQ" autocomplete="postal-code" aria-label="Postcode">
                  <button type="submit" class="qw-cfg-btn ready">Show my dates &rarr;</button>
                </form>
                <div class="qw-cfg-hint"><span class="qw-cfg-hint-muted">Try W1W 8JQ (London) or EH1 1AA (Edinburgh)</span></div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="qw-step" data-hp-step="5" hidden>
              <button class="qw-btn-back" type="button" data-hp-back>&larr; Back</button>
              <div class="qw-diag-card">
                <div class="qw-diag-price">
                  <span class="qw-diag-price-num">{{ diagnostic_fee }}</span>
                  <span class="qw-diag-price-label">paid at booking · repair quoted separately</span>
                </div>
                <ol class="qw-diag-steps">
                  <li><span class="qw-diag-step-n">01</span> Bench diagnosis confirms the exact fault.</li>
                  <li><span class="qw-diag-step-n">02</span> You approve the repair quote before work starts.</li>
                  <li><span class="qw-diag-step-n">03</span> Walk-in, courier and UK mail-in are available.</li>
                </ol>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div class="hp-trust-belowhero">
    <section class="trust-band">
      <div class="container">
        {% render 'hp-trust-card', rating: rating, review_count: review_count %}
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <section class="hp-reviews" id="reviews" data-screen-label="Reviews wall">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hp-reviews-head">
        <div>
          <div class="hp-section-eyebrow">Customer outcomes</div>
          <h2 class="hp-section-title">The hard cases. Real customers.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="reviews-wall-stat" aria-label="{{ review_copy }}">
          <div class="reviews-wall-stat-row">
            <div class="reviews-wall-stat-num">{{ rating }}</div>
            <div class="reviews-wall-stat-stars">{% render 'hp-stars', size: 16 %}</div>
          </div>
          <div class="reviews-wall-stat-meta"><strong>{{ review_count }}</strong> Google reviews</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="reviews-wall-grid">
        <article class="review-card hp-reveal">
          <div class="review-card-top"><span class="review-card-tag">Saved {{ backlight_saving }}</span><div class="review-card-stars">{% render 'hp-stars', size: 11 %}</div></div>
          <h3>Apple said new logic board. It was one chip.</h3>
          <p>Quoted {{ apple_board_quote }} for a board swap. iCorrect traced it to the backlight IC and repaired it under the microscope. Same Mac, my data untouched.</p>
          <footer class="review-card-foot"><strong>Daniel R.</strong><span>MBP 16&quot; M1 Max · Google</span></footer>
        </article>
        <article class="review-card hp-reveal">
          <div class="review-card-top"><span class="review-card-tag">Recovery</span><div class="review-card-stars">{% render 'hp-stars', size: 11 %}</div></div>
          <h3>Liquid damage. They returned my data.</h3>
          <p>Apple wrote it off after a wine spill. Cleaned the board, replaced the flex, recovered every file.</p>
          <footer class="review-card-foot"><strong>Henrietta W.</strong><span>MBA 13&quot; M2 · Google</span></footer>
        </article>
        <article class="review-card hp-reveal">
          <div class="review-card-top"><span class="review-card-tag">Warranty</span><div class="review-card-stars">{% render 'hp-stars', size: 11 %}</div></div>
          <h3>Stage Light gone. Warranty honoured.</h3>
          <p>Classic flex-cable failure. Re-did the work under warranty 9 months later. No quibbles.</p>
          <footer class="review-card-foot"><strong>Marcus T.</strong><span>MBP 16&quot; M1 Max · Google</span></footer>
        </article>
        <article class="review-card hp-reveal">
          <div class="review-card-top"><span class="review-card-tag">Same day</span><div class="review-card-stars">{% render 'hp-stars', size: 11 %}</div></div>
          <h3>Walked in at 9. Working screen by lunch.</h3>
          <p>Genuine display fitted while I worked across the road. The price I was quoted online was the price I paid.</p>
          <footer class="review-card-foot"><strong>Priya S.</strong><span>iPhone 15 Pro · Google</span></footer>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="hp-section hp-datasafety">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hp-section-head">
        <div>
          <div class="hp-section-eyebrow">Data &amp; privacy</div>
          <h2 class="hp-section-title">Your data stays on your device.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="hp-section-lede">We're board-level hardware specialists, not IT support. We don't need your passwords, we don't image your drive, and we don't plug your Mac into our network.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hp-datasafety-grid">
        <div class="hp-datasafety-card hp-reveal"><span class="hp-datasafety-num">01</span><h3>Screen repairs never touch your drive</h3><p>The display is a separate assembly. We replace it without powering on — your data doesn't enter the equation.</p></div>
        <div class="hp-datasafety-card hp-reveal"><span class="hp-datasafety-num">02</span><h3>GDPR-compliant workshop</h3><p>No passcodes requested unless post-repair testing requires it — and you can be present for that step. NDA on request for corporate clients.</p></div>
        <div class="hp-datasafety-card hp-reveal"><span class="hp-datasafety-num">03</span><h3>No cloud, no sync</h3><p>Your device doesn't connect to our network. Diagnosis happens on an isolated bench with board-level tools, not software.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="hp-section hp-priceconf">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hp-section-head">
        <div>
          <div class="hp-section-eyebrow">Pricing</div>
          <h2 class="hp-section-title">The quote is the price. No surprises.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="hp-section-lede">We don't lowball to get you through the door and then discover "additional damage." If diagnosis reveals something we didn't expect, we call you with an updated quote before touching anything.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hp-priceconf-grid">
        <div class="hp-priceconf-card hp-priceconf-card-main">
          <div class="hp-priceconf-row"><span class="hp-priceconf-label">Fixed-price repairs</span><span class="hp-priceconf-value">Screen, battery, rear glass — priced by model, not by mood.</span></div>
          <div class="hp-priceconf-row"><span class="hp-priceconf-label">Bench diagnosis</span><span class="hp-priceconf-value">{{ diagnostic_fee }}, paid at booking, covers bench diagnosis; your repair is quoted separately for approval.</span></div>
          <div class="hp-priceconf-row"><span class="hp-priceconf-label">No hidden fees</span><span class="hp-priceconf-value">The price includes parts, labour, calibration, QA, and a 2-year warranty. Collection and return are the only add-on.</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="hp-priceconf-compare">
          <div class="hp-priceconf-compare-head"><span>Why we're different from Apple</span></div>
          <div class="hp-priceconf-row-compare"><span class="hp-priceconf-compare-label">Backlight IC failure</span><div class="hp-priceconf-compare-prices"><span class="hp-priceconf-compare-theirs">Apple: <strong>{{ apple_board_quote }}</strong> <em>(full board swap)</em></span><span class="hp-priceconf-compare-ours">iCorrect: <strong>{{ backlight_price }}</strong> <em>(chip replacement)</em></span></div></div>
          <div class="hp-priceconf-row-compare"><span class="hp-priceconf-compare-label">MacBook Pro 14&quot; screen</span><div class="hp-priceconf-compare-prices"><span class="hp-priceconf-compare-theirs">Apple: <strong>{{ apple_screen_quote }}</strong></span><span class="hp-priceconf-compare-ours">iCorrect: <strong>{{ macbook_screen_price }}</strong></span></div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="hp-section hp-access">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hp-section-head">
        <div>
          <div class="hp-section-eyebrow">Getting your device to us</div>
          <h2 class="hp-section-title">Three ways in. One standard of repair.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="hp-section-lede">Walk in from Oxford Circus, send a London courier, or post it from anywhere in the UK. Every repair uses the same bench, the same parts, the same warranty.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hp-access-grid">
        <div class="hp-access-card hp-reveal"><div class="hp-access-icon">{% render 'hp-icon-arrow-enter' %}</div><h3 class="hp-access-title">Walk in</h3><div class="hp-access-detail">12 Margaret Street, Fitzrovia W1W 8JQ</div><div class="hp-access-meta">Mon-Fri · no appointment needed</div><p class="hp-access-body">Opposite The London Palladium. Diagnosis while you wait. Most screen and battery repairs returned same-day or next-day.</p></div>
        <div class="hp-access-card hp-reveal"><div class="hp-access-icon">{% render 'hp-icon-briefcase' %}</div><h3 class="hp-access-title">Same-day courier</h3><div class="hp-access-detail">London postcodes only</div><div class="hp-access-meta">+ {{ courier_fee }} · collected within 3 hours</div><p class="hp-access-body">We send a tracked courier to your door. Your device is on the bench the same day, returned as soon as the repair's done.</p></div>
        <div class="hp-access-card hp-reveal"><div class="hp-access-icon">{% render 'hp-icon-calendar' %}</div><h3 class="hp-access-title">UK-wide mail-in</h3><div class="hp-access-detail">Pre-paid tracked shipping</div><div class="hp-access-meta">+ {{ mail_fee }} · next-day collection kit</div><p class="hp-access-body">We send you a pre-paid, insured shipping kit. Post it, we repair it, we courier it back. Same warranty, same quality.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="hp-section hp-corporate">
    <div class="container hp-corporate-inner">
      <div class="hp-corporate-text">
        <div class="hp-section-eyebrow" style="color:#a3a3a3">Specialist &amp; Corporate</div>
        <h2 class="hp-corporate-title">When it's business-critical,<br>skip the queue.</h2>
        <p class="hp-corporate-body">Time-sensitive data recovery. Fleet repairs on retainer. The device Apple said was a write-off that your board presentation lives on. We handle the cases other shops won't touch — and we don't route you through a chatbot to get there.</p>
        <ul class="hp-corporate-list">
          <li>Priority bench slot — same-day or next-day turnaround</li>
          <li>Dedicated technician, not a call centre</li>
          <li>NDA, audit trail, GDPR-compliant handling</li>
          <li>Fleet pricing for 5+ devices</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="/pages/corporate-service" class="hp-corporate-cta">Talk to a specialist &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="hp-corporate-aside">
        <div class="hp-corporate-stat hp-reveal"><span class="hp-corporate-stat-num">94%</span><span class="hp-corporate-stat-label">Data recovered from "dead" Macs in 2025</span></div>
        <div class="hp-corporate-stat hp-reveal"><span class="hp-corporate-stat-num">4 h</span><span class="hp-corporate-stat-label">Average turnaround on priority bench repairs</span></div>
        <div class="hp-corporate-stat hp-reveal"><span class="hp-corporate-stat-num">NDA</span><span class="hp-corporate-stat-label">Signed on request for every corporate job</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="hp-section hp-faq" id="faq">
    <div class="container hp-faq-grid">
      <div class="hp-faq-left">
        <div class="hp-section-eyebrow">Frequently asked</div>
        <h2 class="hp-section-title">Questions, answered honestly.</h2>
        <p class="hp-faq-copy">If your question isn't here, call <a href="tel:+442070998517">+44 (0)207 099 8517</a> or drop in — we're opposite The London Palladium.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hp-faq-right">
        {%- assign faq_questions = 'How long does a repair take?|Are the parts genuine Apple?|Is my data safe?|What does the 2-year warranty cover?|Do I need to book, or can I walk in?|What if Apple says it is unfixable?' | split: '|' -%}
        {%- assign faq_answers = "Most screen and battery repairs are done in 1-2 working days. Walk in before 11am with a common repair and same-day turnaround is usually possible. Board-level work takes 3-5 days because we need to scope, repair, and QA under the microscope.|Yes. We source original Apple displays and batteries where available, calibrate screens in-house, and explain the part option before fitting it.|Completely. Screen and battery repairs do not touch your storage. For board-level work, your device stays on an isolated bench and never connects to our network.|Every part we fit and the labour to install it. If anything we touched fails inside 24 months, we fix it under warranty. Accidental damage is not covered.|Either. Walk in Mon-Fri for diagnosis and a written quote. Booking via the wizard reserves a bench slot and is usually faster, particularly for board-level work or courier collection.|That is what we specialise in. Apple comparison here is about repair approach only: they often replace modules; we repair at component level where it is technically and financially sensible." | split: '|' -%}
        {%- for question in faq_questions -%}
          <div class="hp-faq-item{% if forloop.first %} is-open{% endif %}" data-hp-faq>
            <button type="button" class="hp-faq-q" aria-expanded="{% if forloop.first %}true{% else %}false{% endif %}"><span>{{ question }}</span><span class="hp-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span></button>
            <div class="hp-faq-a" {% unless forloop.first %}hidden{% endunless %}>{{ faq_answers[forloop.index0] }}</div>
          </div>
        {%- endfor -%}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="hp-finalcta">
    <div class="container hp-finalcta-inner">
      <h2>Ready to get it fixed?</h2>
      <p>Tell us your device and the symptom. See your price in 60 seconds — or let us diagnose it properly first.</p>
      <div class="hp-finalcta-row"><a href="#wizard" class="hp-cta hp-cta-primary hp-cta-lg">Get a quote <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="hp-footer">
